text:
Haysville is a city in Sedgwick County, Kansas, United States. It is a suburb of Wichita. In 2010, 10,826 people lived there. Haysville is known as the "Peach Capital of Kansas".
Geography.
Haysville is at (37.563787, -97.353044). The United States Census Bureau says that the city has a total area of. Of that, is land and is water.
People.
Haysville is part of the Wichita, KS Metropolitan Statistical Area.
2010 census.
The 2010 census says that there were 10,826 people, 3,857 households, and 2,932 families living in Haysville.
Government.
The Haysville government has a mayor and eight council members. The council meets the 2nd and 4th Monday of each month at 7PM.
